>   This is a fundamental misunderstanding of the concept of "natural
>law."  Natural law consists of the laws of God not handed down through
>revelations to prophets, but revealed through the laws of nature.  If
>P/=NP, then there is a right to public key cryptography in natural
>law.  There is a fundamental right to privacy in natural law.  Think
>of it as, "If God intended us not to have privacy, everyone would have
>X-ray vision."

